// Adversarial: Voltchain evolution chip (Chain Reaction x1 + Damage Boost x2) is injected via
// chip_selections. Voltchain fires chain lightning between cells on cell impact — each arc
// travels to nearby targets and can trigger secondary cell destructions, creating cascade chains.
// Dense layout under Perfect input maximises simultaneous cell impacts across 8000 frames, which
// drives the maximum number of overlapping chain-lightning spawns. Godmode breaker guarantees
// infinite play for sustained cascade buildup. The adversarial risk: if arc entities are not
// cleaned up after chain completion (target destroyed mid-flight, no reachable next target, or
// chain-length exceeded), ChainArcCountReasonable fires. Simultaneous cascades from multiple
// Voltchain triggers can create enough in-flight arcs to exhaust the default 50-entity ceiling
// if any arc-or-chain entity leaks. NoEntityLeaks detects orphaned ChainLightningChain/Arc
// entities that survive past their expected cleanup frame. NoNaN guards against position
// corruption from mid-flight target despawn. BoltSpeedAccurate catches any physics corruption
// from the arc-damage application path.
(
    breaker: "godmode",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Perfect(AlwaysPerfect),
    max_frames: 4000,
    disallowed_failures: [ChainArcCountReasonable, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN, BoltSpeedAccurate],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 4321,
    chip_selections: ["Voltchain"],
)
